<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
<a class="spoiler" href="/questions/436145-i-ve-searched-for-online-reviews-perhaps">This question contains spoilers...</a>
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[I've searched for online reviews (perhaps in denial!?) because I couldn't quite believe if I was reading too much into the last twin scene and whether they did actually sleep together? Is there any chance that this can simply mean something deeper and we all just think it means they sleep together? or do I have to face facts? I finished this book a few days ago now and it is still affecting me! Help? <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
