<div id="review_2003819293" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2003819293" />
    <a title="~Jo~" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28323108-jo"><img alt="~Jo~" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627473933p2/28323108.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2003819293?book_show_action=true">May 01, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="~Jo~" class="user" itemprop="url" name="~Jo~" href="/user/show/28323108-jo">~Jo~</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/117661.The_God_of_Small_Things">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28323108-jo?shelf=to-throw-from-a-high-building">to-throw-from-a-high-building</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28323108-jo?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2003819293" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7618976919213763837">If one ever has trouble sleeping at night, then I highly recommend &quot;The God of small things&quot;. It has been tried and tested by yours truly, and quite honestly, this is one of the most underwhelming books that I&apos;ve read in a good while. <br/><br/>This won the Booker prize in 1997, and reading some of the positive reviews on here, I was expecting to be truly dazzled. I hear that this book is important. Important to whom exactly? I felt nothing for this. <br/><br/>I think I can address the main issue immediately, that </span>
  <span id="freeText7618976919213763837" style="display:none">If one ever has trouble sleeping at night, then I highly recommend "The God of small things". It has been tried and tested by yours truly, and quite honestly, this is one of the most underwhelming books that I've read in a good while. <br /><br />This won the Booker prize in 1997, and reading some of the positive reviews on here, I was expecting to be truly dazzled. I hear that this book is important. Important to whom exactly? I felt nothing for this. <br /><br />I think I can address the main issue immediately, that being, I just couldn't follow what was written. The plot was everywhere. It didn't feel smoothly written, the plot was detached which mostly lead to a great deal of confusion and irritation on my end. There were lots of flashbacks, which made the present tense storyline disorientated. <br /><br />Now, I love beautiful writing, but this became incredibly tedious. There were SO many metaphors thrown in, and it was difficult to recognise if I was reading something significant to the plot or not. It just didn't work, and, there is a such word called "overuse". <br /><br />I cannot go into considerable detail about the characters, as the character development was basically non existent. There were a good amount of characters in this book, and by the end of the book, they were still just names to me. <br /><br />This book for me, was comparable to one of those mud pies, that you make as a kid, in which you add a bit of everything to, grass, stones, your dads gardening gloves, your ghostbuster figures, and eventually, what you get, is one huge, confused mess. <br /><br />TIP: Never trust a Booker prize winner.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7618976919213763837" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


