<span id="freeTextContainer6638389149848092239"><b>3.5</b><br/>I usually love books that are set in the Indian subcontinent but found this one frustrating to be honest.<br/>On the one hand it was a tour de force of sumptuous prose, but on the other I found that the narrative meandered all over the place, making it difficult to for me (with my grasshopper brain) to keep up.<br/>Although Roy&apos;s writing is kissed by the gods, I&apos;m a great believer in a story&apos;s need to flow and my early enthusiasm became steadily dampened as the book progressed.</span>
  <span id="freeText6638389149848092239" style="display:none"><b>3.5</b><br />I usually love books that are set in the Indian subcontinent but found this one frustrating to be honest.<br />On the one hand it was a tour de force of sumptuous prose, but on the other I found that the narrative meandered all over the place, making it difficult to for me (with my grasshopper brain) to keep up.<br />Although Roy's writing is kissed by the gods, I'm a great believer in a story's need to flow and my early enthusiasm became steadily dampened as the book progressed.</span>
