<div id="review_1784752" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1784752" />
    <a title="Celeste Ng" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/80835-celeste-ng"><img alt="Celeste Ng" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442458318p2/80835.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1784752?book_show_action=true">Jun 08, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Celeste Ng" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Celeste Ng" href="/user/show/80835-celeste-ng">Celeste Ng</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1784752" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10503706595035739355">As soon as I finished reading it, I literally turned it over and began reading it again. (Later, I discovered that a reviewer said and did the exact same thing!) This book is incredibly crafted--in plot, in structure, in language, in emotion. I read it to remind myself of that kind of book I hope to write someday. One of my all-time top-5 desert island books.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


